SIMPLE: fertilization
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fertilization
<hw>Fer`ti*li*za"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act or process of rendering fertile.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The act of fecundating or
impregnating animal or vegetable germs; esp., the process by which in
flowers the pollen renders the ovule fertile, or an analogous process in
flowerless plants; fecundation; impregnation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Close fertilization</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>the
fertilization of pistils by pollen derived from the stamens of the same
blossom.</cd> -- <col><b>Cross fertilization</b></col>,
<cd>fertilization by pollen from some other blossom. See under
<er>Cross</er>, <pos>a.</pos></cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fertilize</ent>⟦br⟧
